(2915, 'Reproductive Health & Family Planning', 'Study MCQs', 'During which trimester does the baby’s major organs begin to develop?', '["First trimester", "Second trimester", "Third trimester Answer: A. First trimester 2.What is the average length of a full-term pregnancy in weeks? A.32 weeks B.38 weeks C.42 weeks Answer: B. 38 weeks 3.What is the medical term for the release of an egg from the ovary during the menstrual cycle? A.Implantation B.Ovulation C.Fertilization Answer: B. Ovulation 4.What is the purpose of the amniotic fluidduring pregnancy? A.To provide nutrients to the baby B.To cushion and protect the baby C.To regulate the baby''s temperature Answer: B. To cushion and protect the baby 5.Which hormone isresponsible for maintaining the uterine lining during pregnancy? A.Estrogen B.Progesterone C.Human Chorionic Gonadotropin (hCG) Answer: B. Progesterone 6.What term isused to describe the firstmovement of the baby in the womb that can be feltby the mother? A.Quickening B.Braxton Hicks contractions C.Labor Answer: A. Quickening 7.What is the name of the condition characterized by high blood pressure during pregnancy? A.Gestational diabetes B.Preeclampsia C.Ectopic pregnancy Answer: B. Preeclampsia 8.How many weeks is a typical pregnancy considered full-term? A.32 weeks B.38 weeks C.42 weeks Answer: B. 38 weeks 9.What is the name of the procedure used to confirm pregnancy by detecting the hormone hCG in the urine or blood? A.Ultrasound B.Amniocentesis C.Pregnancy test Answer: C. Pregnancy test 10. Which of the following is a common symptom of pregnancy? A.Increased energy levels B.Decreased sense of smell C.Morning sickness Answer: C. Morning sickness 11. What is the medical term for the fertilized egg implanted in the uterus? A.Embryo B.Zygote C.Blastocyst Answer: A. Embryo 12. What is the name of the structure that connects the baby to the placenta fornutrient exchange? A.Umbilical cord B.Amniotic sac C.Placenta Answer: A. Umbilical cord 13. How many weeks are in a typical pregnancy? A.30 weeks B.40 weeks C.50 weeks Answer: B. 40 weeks 14. What is the name of the condition where a fertilized egg implants outside of the uterus? A.Miscarriage B.Ectopic pregnancy C.Stillbirth Answer: B. Ectopic pregnancy 15. Which of the following vitamins is important forfetal development during pregnancy? A.Vitamin A B.Vitamin D C.Folic Acid Answer: C. Folic Acid 16. What is the term for the age of the pregnancy calculated from the firstday of the last menstrual period? A.Gestational age B.Fetal age C.Conception age Answer: A. Gestational age 17. What is the name of the condition where a pregnant woman experiences high blood sugar levels? A.Gestational diabetes B.Type 1 diabetes C.Type 2 diabetes Answer: A. Gestational diabetes 18. What is the process inwhich the baby moves into the birth canal during labor? A.Dilation B.Effacement C.Engagement Answer: C. Engagement 19. Which test is used to monitor your baby''s heart rate during pregnancy and labor? A.Fetal Kick Count B.Non-Stress Test C.Amniocentesis Answer: B. Non-Stress Test 20. What is the name of the hormone that begins the process of labor and delivery? A.Oxytocin B.Progesterone C.Human Chorionic Gonadotropin (hCG) Answer: A. Oxytocin 21. What is the term for the procedure where a baby is born through an incision in the mother''s abdomen? A.Cesarean section B.Episiotomy C.Vacuum extraction Answer: A. Cesarean section 22. What is the name for the uterine contractions that help the cervix to dilate during labor? A.Braxton Hicks contractions B.Contractions C.Labor pains Answer: A. Braxton Hicks contractions 23. Which of the following isnot a common sign of labor? A.Contractions B.Water breaking C.Decreased fetal movement Answer: C. Decreased fetal movement 24. What is the stage of labor during which the cervix dilates fully to 10 cm? A.Stage 1 B.Stage 2 C.Stage 3 Answer: A. Stage 1 25. What is the name of the surgical procedure to remove the products of conception from the uterus? A.Dilation and curettage (D&C) B.Hysterectomy C.Tubal ligation Answer: A. Dilation and curettage (D&C) 26. Which of the following is a common side effect of pregnancy known as swelling in the extremities? A.Edema B.Braxton Hicks contractions C.Placenta previa Answer: A. Edema 27. What is the term for the expulsion of the placenta after childbirth? A.Afterbirth B.Postpartum hemorrhage C.Placental abruption Answer: A. Afterbirth 28. What is the name of the process where the baby moves into a head-down position in the uterus? A.Engagement B.Breech C.Transverse Answer: A. Engagement 29. How many stages are there in the process of labor and delivery? A. 2 stages B.3 stages C. 4 stages Answer: B. 3 stages 30. What is the name of the condition where the uterus slips into the vagina instead of pushing a baby out? A. Uterine inversion B.Uterine prolapse C. Uterine rupture Answer: A. Uterine inversion 31. What is the name of the medication used to induce labor or strengthen contractions? A. Cervidil B.Pitocin C. Prostaglandin Answer: B. Pitocin 32. What is the term for a pregnancy that ends before the 20th week? A. Premature birth B.Stillbirth C. Miscarriage Answer: C. Miscarriage 33. What is the name of the condition where the placenta covers part or allof the cervix? A. Placenta previa B.Placental abruption C. Ectopic pregnancy Answer: A. Placenta previa 34. What is the name of the surgical procedure to ligate the fallopian tubes? A. Tubal ligation B.Hysterectomy C. Uterine fibroid embolization Answer: A. Tubal ligation 35. What is the term for the process of allowing the cervix to thin and open during labor? A. Dilation B.Effacement C. Engagement Answer: B. Effacement 36. Which of the following is not a common method of inducing labor? A. Breaking the water B.Pitocin C. C-section Answer: C. C-section 37. What is the name of the condition where the placenta separates from the uterine wall before delivery? A.Placenta previa B.Placental abruption C.Ectopic pregnancy Answer: B. Placental abruption 38. What is the term for the period immediately following childbirth? A.Postpartum B.Prenatal C.Antepartum Answer: A. Postpartum 39. What is the name of the condition where a woman experiences a pregnancy that ends after the 20th week? A.Stillbirth B.Miscarriage C.Preterm birth Answer: A. Stillbirth 40. What is the term for a baby born before 37 weeks of pregnancy? A.Preterm B.Post-term C.Full-term Answer: A. Preterm 41. What is the term for the process of the baby moving through the birth canal during delivery? A.Engagement B.Delivery C.Labor Answer: B. Delivery 42. What is the term for the thinning and opening of the cervix during labor? A.Dilation B.Effacement C.Engagement Answer: B. Effacement 43. Which of the following is a common symptom of labor? A.Back pain B.Decreased appetite C.Decreased urination Answer: A. Back pain 44. What is the name of the procedure used to monitor the health of the unborn baby during pregnancy? A.Ultrasound B.Non-stress test C.Amniocentesis Answer: A. Ultrasound 45. What is the term for the procedure where a needle is inserted into the amniotic sac to gather fluidfor testing? A.Ultrasound B.Amniocentesis C.Non-stress test Answer: B. Amniocentesis 46. What is the term for the firstbowel movement of a newborn baby? A.Meconium B.Vernix C.Lanugo Answer: A. Meconium 47. What is the name of the condition where the baby isin a breech position before delivery? A.Engagement B.Breech C.Transverse Answer: B. Breech 48. Which of the following is a common sign of preterm labor? A.Weight gain B.Vaginal bleeding C.Decreased fetal movement Answer: B. Vaginal bleeding 49. What is the term for the tissue that connects the baby to the placenta for nutrient exchange? A.Umbilical cord B.Amniotic sac C.Placenta Answer: A. Umbilical cord 50. What is the name of the condition where a woman carries more than one baby in her uterus? A.Monozygotic pregnancy B.Fraternal pregnancy C.Multiple gestation Answer: C. Multiple gestation Section C 1.Which stage of labor ischaracterized by the cervix dilating to 10 centimeters? A.Stage 1 B.Stage 2 C.Stage 3", "Stage 4"]'::jsonb, 0, '', 'Obstetric & Neonatal', '🤱', true),
